> prior to his election to the county commission in 2004, commissioner nodine worked in the political arena as a political and media consultant as well as a city council person for the city of mobile. most recently, he helped secure thyssenkrupp, one of the largest economic development projects in alabama history. commissioner nodine is also involved in the mobile boys and girls club. he is the president of the mobile business and professional association, co-founder of the mobile jump start juvenile boot camp program. he is a member of the board of advisors for the mobile county chamber of commerce as well as the alabama state port authority. commissioner nodine is a former aide to former nato commander general alexander haig. he also served under governor haley barbour as advance coordinator for the (PARTY NAME) national committee in 1988 and worked on george h.w. bush's 1989 inaugural team. commissioner nodine resides in mobile with his family. <br/></p></span>



